  <brief_title>Pharmaco-Economic Study Of Ultiva In Intensive Care Unit(ICU)Subjects</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Centre-Randomized, Open-Label, Cross-Over Study to Compare the Pharmaco-Economic Consequences of an Ultiva (Remifentanil Hydrochloride) Based Regimen With Conventional Sedative Based Regimens in ICU Subjects Requiring Short-Term Mechanical Ventilation With Analgesia and Sedation</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>GlaxoSmithKline</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>GlaxoSmithKline</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study will evaluate the pharmaco-economic consequences of the use of a remifentanil based
      regimen compared with a conventional sedative based regimen in terms of duration of
      mechanical ventilation, length of stay in ICU, difference in extubation time and use of
      concomitant sedative agents.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
